billboarder()%>%bb_piechart(data=t)

from above boxplot we would predict that, all numeric columns i.e sepal length, sepal width,petal length,petal width,petal width are effected on species.

Now we want to predict the species category based on that 4 numeric features or columns so we are going to classification algorithms

KNN

split the data into train and test set.

library(caret)
## Loading required package: lattice
set.seed(18)## set the seed to stabilize our output 
partition=createDataPartition(y=iris$Species,p=0.7,list = FALSE)

iris_train=iris[partition,]
iris_test=iris[-partition,]
dim(iris_train)
## [1] 105   5
dim(iris_test)
## [1] 45  5

fit the model

fit_knn=knn3(Species~.,data = iris_train[1:5],k=5)

prediction

iris_predk=predict(fit_knn,newdata = iris_test[,-5],type = "class")

model evaluation (check accuracy of the model)

tl_1=table(iris_predk,iris_test[,5],dnn = list('pred','actual'))
confusionMatrix(tl_1)

Decision Tree

fit model

library(rpart)
library(rpart.plot)
iris_tree=rpart(Species~.,data = iris_train,method = "class")
rpart.plot(iris_tree)

from above tree plot we get the species classification criteria : when petal.length < 2.5 then species category is setosa. when petal.length>2.5, Petal.width<1.6 then species category is versicolor. when petal.length>2.5, petal.width>1.6 then species category is virginica.

Prediction

pred_dt=predict(iris_tree,iris_test[,-5],type = "class")

model Evaluation

tbl_dt=table(pred_dt,iris_test[,5],dnn = list('pred','actual'))
